WEBVTT

00:02.168 --> 00:03.585
NARRATOR:
Previously on Vampire Diaries:

00:03.753 --> 00:07.798
Vampires and werewolves used to roam
until a shaman put a curse on them.

00:07.966 --> 00:11.677
Werewolves can only turn on a full moon
and vampires are weakened by the sun.

00:11.845 --> 00:15.597
You're saying, the oldest vampire in
the history of time is coming after me?

00:15.765 --> 00:19.810
Klaus is the most feared of the Originals,
but I'm here to offer you a deal.

00:19.978 --> 00:22.646
You trust Elijah? He's an Original.
He can't be trusted.

00:22.814 --> 00:26.400
Elena told me you're both working
for Elijah. So don't lie about it.

00:26.568 --> 00:29.737
- I'm Jules. I know you're a werewolf.
- Do you know where Mason is?

00:29.904 --> 00:31.905
- He's dead.
- I don't know who to trust.

00:32.073 --> 00:34.450
You stood there when
they were going to kill us?

00:34.617 --> 00:36.618
You stood there.
You didn't do anything.

00:36.786 --> 00:38.912
- I didn't know what to do.
- It's too late.

00:39.080 --> 00:40.748
Because we're not friends anymore.

00:40.915 --> 00:43.417
- Thanks for coming.
- I'm not afraid of a vampire.

00:43.585 --> 00:46.837
- We will take you.
- I'm not so sure about that, tough guy.

00:47.714 --> 00:49.840
[SHOUTING]

00:50.008 --> 00:52.885
Elijah made a promise to Elena.
I'm here to see it's upheld.

00:53.053 --> 00:55.054
I don't know what Mason
was doing here.

00:55.221 --> 00:57.556
Because of this rock
he was trying to find.

00:57.724 --> 00:58.974
- What rock?
TYLER: A moonstone.

00:59.142 --> 01:01.060
- Where is it now?
- I couldn't tell you.

01:34.052 --> 01:35.636
Go ahead, tell her.

01:36.387 --> 01:39.765
Let me just preface this
with a big disclaimer that screams:

01:39.933 --> 01:42.684
- "I should have known better."
- What is it, Stevie?

01:42.852 --> 01:44.603
When Brady told me what Tyler said...

01:44.771 --> 01:46.522
...about Mason being here
for the moonstone...

01:46.689 --> 01:50.025
...something clicked.
There was this moment back in Florida...

01:50.193 --> 01:52.361
...when I suspected Mason was
up to something.

01:52.529 --> 01:56.115
He was banging that hot vampire, Kathy,
and he didn't want anyone to know.

01:56.282 --> 01:59.409
- All right. Just get to the point.
- That is the point, Jules.

02:00.912 --> 02:02.287
It's the sun and moon curse.

02:05.083 --> 02:08.043
Mason was asking me
all kinds of questions about it.

02:08.211 --> 02:09.627
If it could be broken.

02:09.795 --> 02:12.881
And when that evil man-witch
showed up last night, double-click.

02:13.049 --> 02:15.551
Witches, vampires, moonstone.

02:15.718 --> 02:18.470
They're putting everything in place
to break the curse.

02:19.764 --> 02:21.974
We can't let them do that...

02:22.642 --> 02:26.019
...even if we have to kill
every last vampire in this town.

02:37.615 --> 02:39.491
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

02:39.993 --> 02:41.076
CAROLINE: Go away.
ELENA: Mm.

02:41.244 --> 02:43.036
[ELENA GRUNTS]

02:43.204 --> 02:44.538
[BONNIE GRUNTS]

02:47.041 --> 02:48.167
[SIGHS]

02:49.294 --> 02:50.544
- Hello?
- Unh.

02:50.712 --> 02:51.920
- Elena.
- Shh.

02:52.338 --> 02:54.256
STEFAN:
How was the slumber party?

02:54.424 --> 02:58.385
Unh. Good. Heh, much needed.

02:58.553 --> 03:01.305
- When can you and I have one?
- Mm.

03:01.472 --> 03:02.681
That can be arranged.

03:02.849 --> 03:06.476
Okay. Now. Today.

03:06.644 --> 03:08.312
Take me far, far away.

03:08.479 --> 03:12.232
- Even with everything that's going on?
- Because of everything that's going on.

03:12.817 --> 03:16.153
And you're sure this has nothing to do
with dodging your father...

03:16.321 --> 03:18.488
...who just got into town?
- Uh, heh...

03:18.656 --> 03:20.449
This has everything to do with that.

03:20.992 --> 03:23.160
Well, in that case,
where would you like to go?

03:23.328 --> 03:24.411
[CHUCKLES]

03:25.246 --> 03:27.831
I'm late. This is such a crazy day.

03:28.291 --> 03:32.294
I'm, uh, covering
the Historical Society's high tea.

03:32.462 --> 03:34.004
Woo-hoo! Thrilling.

03:34.172 --> 03:36.006
Yeah, it's for some visiting writer.

03:36.174 --> 03:38.342
He's writing a book
on small-town Virginia.

03:38.509 --> 03:40.177
It's a big snooze, heh.

03:40.345 --> 03:42.304
- Writer? What's his name?
- Mm-hm.

03:42.472 --> 03:44.431
Uh, Elijah Smith.

03:44.599 --> 03:47.392
- Smith. He's using Smith?
- Mm-hm. Heh.

03:47.560 --> 03:50.395
Okay. You have your story
straight in your mind, right?

03:50.563 --> 03:52.981
I can't say that you bit me
or drank my blood...

03:53.149 --> 03:56.401
...just that we hit it off
and I really like you.

03:56.694 --> 03:58.195
You are terrific, though.

03:58.363 --> 04:01.114
You're sweet, funny, you're honest.

04:01.491 --> 04:02.991
DAMON:
And you're falling hard.

04:03.326 --> 04:04.409
ANDIE:
You might be the one.

04:04.577 --> 04:05.702
Perfect.

04:09.791 --> 04:11.833
- Have a great day, honey.
- Mwah.

04:12.543 --> 04:15.295
Oh, hey, Alaric, heh. Later.

04:18.298 --> 04:19.466
DAMON:
My new girlfriend.

04:19.634 --> 04:22.970
- Andie Starr, Action News.
- It's not called Action News.

04:23.137 --> 04:25.514
Yeah, I know. I just like saying it.
Come on.

04:26.432 --> 04:29.851
So John Gilbert gave me this
to kill Elijah.

04:30.436 --> 04:33.647
Said you have to dip the dagger
in the remains of an ash tree...

04:33.815 --> 04:37.067
...that dates back to the Originals.
If there's any truth in that.

04:37.235 --> 04:39.778
- You think it's a set-up?
- Could be. Guy's a weasel.

04:39.946 --> 04:42.656
Wouldn't put anything past him.
What are you up to today?

04:42.824 --> 04:45.284
Jenna and I are supposed to go
to her lake house...

04:45.451 --> 04:47.119
...but somehow we both got roped...

04:47.287 --> 04:50.330
...into doing this Historical Society thing
at the Lockwoods'.

04:50.540 --> 04:52.165
Where Elijah's the guest of honor.

04:52.333 --> 04:55.877
- You're not gonna kill him at the party.
- No, heh, that would be stupid.

04:57.880 --> 05:00.257
I wanna know his endgame
before I kill him.

05:00.425 --> 05:03.468
But I do think it's time
Elijah and I officially met.

05:03.636 --> 05:07.014
Okay, so tell me about this big
witchy plan you've been cooking up.

05:07.181 --> 05:09.516
We don't know the extent
of what Elijah's up to.

05:09.684 --> 05:10.851
No, we don't.

05:11.060 --> 05:14.563
- I ask Luka to tell me what he knows.
- He's not gonna tell you anything.

05:14.731 --> 05:16.898
I didn't say
he was gonna have a choice.

05:18.276 --> 05:19.818
What?

05:24.866 --> 05:26.074
What's that about?

05:27.827 --> 05:31.288
I don't know.
I thought that we were...

05:31.456 --> 05:32.497
[CHUCKLES]

05:32.999 --> 05:34.833
I don't know.

05:44.385 --> 05:46.636
Tyler. Hi.

05:46.804 --> 05:48.764
- Still here.
- Is that all right with you?

05:48.931 --> 05:51.058
That guy made it clear
you needed to go.

05:51.225 --> 05:52.726
And we will. Soon.

05:56.814 --> 05:59.858
Listen, we kind of need your help
with something.

06:00.526 --> 06:02.277
Help us find the moonstone.

06:02.779 --> 06:05.572
Explain to me what the big deal is
about a rock.

06:05.740 --> 06:08.950
That rock helps break the curse
of the sun and the moon.

06:09.202 --> 06:10.619
I don't know what that means.

06:10.787 --> 06:13.955
It's an old curse placed
on both vampires and werewolves.

06:14.123 --> 06:17.084
Vampires break the curse,
they're free to walk in sunlight...

06:17.251 --> 06:20.962
...but we're stuck only turning at the full
moon, a.k.a. Werewolf armageddon.

06:21.130 --> 06:22.672
If we break it, they're stuck...

06:22.840 --> 06:25.342
...and we can turn
whenever we want.

06:25.510 --> 06:27.386
A.k.a. Werewolf domination.

06:28.054 --> 06:29.304
[SIGHS]

06:29.889 --> 06:33.642
Tyler, if we can turn at will,
that means we never have to turn at all.

06:34.310 --> 06:35.727
Not if we don't want to.

06:37.021 --> 06:40.023
- I'd never have to turn again?
- There's more. Stevie?

06:40.191 --> 06:42.359
If vamps are gearing up
to break the curse...

06:42.527 --> 06:45.445
...they have found the doppelgänger.
- The doppelgänger?

06:45.655 --> 06:47.364
Evil-twin shadow person.

06:47.657 --> 06:50.283
We're betting Mason's chick Kathy
knows all about it...

06:50.451 --> 06:52.494
...so we need you to help us
find Kathy.

06:52.870 --> 06:54.788
I have, uh, a picture.

06:55.331 --> 06:57.666
Mason brought her to the bar once.

06:57.834 --> 07:00.919
No one liked her. She was a vampire.
Bad news.

07:01.087 --> 07:04.214
Right here. The girl next to Mason.

07:06.342 --> 07:07.426
That's Elena Gilbert.

07:08.511 --> 07:10.095
You know her?

07:10.471 --> 07:11.930
I've known her my whole life.

07:17.186 --> 07:18.228
Hi.

07:18.396 --> 07:20.856
I'm working.

07:21.315 --> 07:25.402
Yeah, I can see that,
but can you work and talk?

07:25.570 --> 07:26.653
What do you want?

07:26.821 --> 07:31.032
I wanna talk about what we were
supposed to talk about last night...

07:31.200 --> 07:33.201
...before I had to cancel on you.

07:33.369 --> 07:35.579
Yeah, I want us to clear up
the weirdness.

07:35.746 --> 07:39.249
I just want us to talk about us.

07:39.417 --> 07:41.168
Now you're just making it worse.

07:41.335 --> 07:45.422
Uh, I, heh... I don't know
what's going on, Matt.

07:45.590 --> 07:48.300
Where were you last night
when you were supposed to be with me?

07:48.468 --> 07:50.135
- Uh, I...
- Don't say you were with Bonnie...

07:50.303 --> 07:53.513
...because Bonnie was here.
I saw her.

07:59.479 --> 08:00.604
Oh.

08:00.897 --> 08:02.397
Yeah.

08:02.773 --> 08:03.857
Matt?

08:04.025 --> 08:05.192
[SIGHS]

08:08.279 --> 08:09.988
TYLER:
Caroline.

08:10.156 --> 08:12.866
- You stay away from me.
- Look, it's important.

08:13.951 --> 08:16.870
Just stop it, Tyler, okay?
You're just making it worse.

08:17.038 --> 08:20.499
I'm sorry about what happened but
there's so much we need to talk about.

08:20.666 --> 08:22.876
I said, just leave me alone.

08:28.382 --> 08:32.177
Two of you wanna get together, fine.
There's nothing I can do about it...

08:32.345 --> 08:34.346
...but do me a favor,
stop lying about it.

08:34.514 --> 08:37.182
- Matt, there's nothing going on.
- Hey.

08:37.350 --> 08:40.393
I said, stop lying.

08:48.277 --> 08:51.905
STEFAN: Ready for our romantic weekend?
ELENA: Heh, beyond ready.

08:52.281 --> 08:54.950
Let's go before John shows up
and pretends to be a concerned father.

08:55.117 --> 08:56.117
[CELL PHONE BUZZES]

08:56.285 --> 08:58.036
Hmm, I'll go put these in the car.

09:05.670 --> 09:08.463
Uh, please tell me
there's nothing wrong.

09:09.632 --> 09:11.550
[BUZZES]

09:12.718 --> 09:14.594
Nothing's wrong.

09:14.804 --> 09:17.556
Just Caroline. Come on. Let's go.

09:24.230 --> 09:27.566
She's going to Dunham Lake.
Her family has a house up there.

09:27.733 --> 09:29.025
Nice.

09:29.193 --> 09:31.528
Let's go get our doppelgänger.

09:52.883 --> 09:54.676
You all right?

09:55.011 --> 09:58.346
I'm good. I just haven't been back here
since before.

10:00.683 --> 10:02.809
Oh, my God.

10:05.187 --> 10:07.731
Elena, listen,
just say the word, all right?

10:07.898 --> 10:11.192
We'll get back on that highway,
we'll go anywhere else.

10:13.070 --> 10:14.362
I've always loved it here.

10:14.530 --> 10:17.365
I want it to stay that way.
I was just...

10:18.409 --> 10:19.534
...having a moment.

10:23.039 --> 10:24.497
[CHUCKLES]

10:33.424 --> 10:35.508
You don't have to wait there.
I'm all good.

10:35.676 --> 10:38.511
Oh, that's great because I'm, uh...

10:39.555 --> 10:40.930
I'm stuck.

10:43.351 --> 10:45.602
Oh, my God. You can't get in.

10:45.811 --> 10:51.316
Not gonna be a very romantic weekend
unless you, uh, invite me inside.

10:52.193 --> 10:54.402
- Stefan, I can't.
- What?

10:54.570 --> 10:56.905
My parents left this place
to John Gilbert.

10:57.073 --> 10:59.115
He's the only one
who can invite you in.

10:59.325 --> 11:01.242
I'm sorry. I completely forgot.

11:01.410 --> 11:02.744
You're kidding me, right?

11:05.331 --> 11:09.084
Stefan Salvatore,
I hereby invite you into this home, heh.

11:09.251 --> 11:10.710
You are such a liar.

11:10.878 --> 11:13.254
Heh, hey. Hey. Hey.

11:23.099 --> 11:25.266
CAROL: You spent much time
in Richmond for your book?

11:25.434 --> 11:27.268
There's such a wealth of history there.

11:27.436 --> 11:31.106
No. I'm focusing mostly
on the, uh, smaller regions of Virginia.

11:31.273 --> 11:34.734
- Lots of research. Strictly academic.
- That's fascinating.

11:35.444 --> 11:37.487
Damon? What are you doing here?

11:37.655 --> 11:39.280
Hi. You came.

11:39.448 --> 11:41.658
- Hi.
- Hi.

11:43.869 --> 11:46.246
- Thanks for introducing us, Jenna.
- Heh.

11:48.874 --> 11:50.417
[SIGHS]

11:50.584 --> 11:51.793
Wow.

11:51.961 --> 11:54.254
- Damon, what a surprise.
- Carol. Hi.

11:55.506 --> 11:59.175
Hi. Elijah, I want you to meet
Damon Salvatore.

11:59.385 --> 12:01.803
His family is one of Mystic Falls'
founding families.

12:01.971 --> 12:03.555
Mm-hm.

12:04.390 --> 12:07.809
- Such a pleasure to meet you.
- No, pleasure's mine.

12:10.187 --> 12:12.188
[UPBEAT ROCK MUSIC
PLAYING OVER STEREO]

12:15.317 --> 12:16.651
Come bearing coffee gifts.

12:17.486 --> 12:18.820
So you're talking to me now.

12:18.988 --> 12:23.032
I found out what your dad did,
saving my friends from the wolf pack.

12:23.200 --> 12:24.993
Well, had I known that's all it took.

12:25.161 --> 12:27.662
JEREMY: Hey, how's it going?
- What are you doing here?

12:27.830 --> 12:31.499
Bonnie called, I wanted to help.
How's it going?

12:31.667 --> 12:33.460
She's selling it and he's buying it.

12:35.337 --> 12:39.716
- She's giving him the sex smile.
- Yeah, all right, Caroline. I get it.

12:43.554 --> 12:45.138
What you say? Wanna play a game?

12:45.306 --> 12:46.389
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

12:46.557 --> 12:48.683
- Yeah.
- Okay.

12:53.564 --> 12:55.940
What's happening to me?

12:56.192 --> 12:57.525
You're gonna be okay.

12:57.693 --> 12:59.027
Ooh.

12:59.195 --> 13:01.321
Why don't we go over here?

13:01.655 --> 13:03.740
I got him, I got him.

13:05.659 --> 13:07.368
What kind of witch roofie was that?

13:07.536 --> 13:09.704
A strong one.

13:15.836 --> 13:18.046
Having another moment?

13:19.215 --> 13:20.590
[ELENA SIGHS]

13:22.468 --> 13:27.430
Jeremy broke his arm diving off this dock
when he was 6.

13:27.598 --> 13:31.267
My dad taught me how to fish
right off the edge over there.

13:32.394 --> 13:33.686
So many memories.

13:34.355 --> 13:36.731
Do you ever think about us?

13:37.983 --> 13:40.902
What our future will be like,
our memories?

13:41.862 --> 13:45.740
I think there are a lot of conversations
to be had about our future...

13:46.867 --> 13:49.202
...about the kind of life
we could have together.

13:49.870 --> 13:54.374
Now, there's a box
that we shouldn't open.

13:54.542 --> 13:56.584
Oh, we can open it.

13:57.628 --> 13:59.754
Whenever you're ready.

14:00.130 --> 14:04.008
No. I'd rather just be here.

14:04.593 --> 14:05.593
Now.

14:06.595 --> 14:09.430
You know, this is a future memory.

14:11.267 --> 14:15.228
It's where your boyfriend
whispered to you...

14:16.522 --> 14:18.606
...that he loved you.

14:21.068 --> 14:22.569
[WHISPERS]
I love you.

14:22.736 --> 14:24.028
[CHUCKLES]

14:29.243 --> 14:30.827
[ALL CHATTERING]

14:37.293 --> 14:38.918
What's Damon doing with Elijah?

14:39.086 --> 14:41.588
- How would I know?
- Because you're his little helper.

14:41.755 --> 14:42.922
If you say so, John.

14:43.090 --> 14:46.134
Does Jenna know about
your extracurricular activities?

14:46.302 --> 14:48.636
Maybe it's time we tell her.

14:48.804 --> 14:50.847
I mean, she can't stay
in the dark forever.

14:52.099 --> 14:53.141
You're a dick.

14:53.851 --> 14:54.893
I don't think...

14:55.060 --> 14:56.853
...you should sleep over anymore.
- Mm?

14:57.021 --> 15:00.106
It's inappropriate with children
in the house.

15:00.274 --> 15:02.692
And that ring that Isobel gave you?

15:02.860 --> 15:05.820
That's mine.
I'm gonna want that back.

15:06.196 --> 15:07.322
Hmm.

15:12.828 --> 15:16.164
ELIJAH: What can I do for you, Damon?
- I was hoping we could have a word.

15:16.332 --> 15:18.207
- Where is Elena?
- Safe with Stefan.

15:18.375 --> 15:21.044
They're laying low.
You know, bit of a werewolf problem.

15:21.211 --> 15:22.795
Oh, yeah. I heard about that.

15:22.963 --> 15:25.506
I'm sure, since it was your witch
that saved the day.

15:25.674 --> 15:28.009
- You are welcome.
- Which adds to my confusion...

15:28.177 --> 15:29.719
...of exactly why you're here.

15:29.887 --> 15:32.639
Why don't you just stay focused
on keeping Elena safe...

15:32.806 --> 15:34.515
...and leave the rest to me.

15:36.852 --> 15:38.227
Not good enough.

15:40.731 --> 15:41.856
[DAMON GRUNTING]

15:48.697 --> 15:51.824
You young vampires,
you're so arrogant.

15:53.035 --> 15:55.161
How dare you come in here
and challenge me?

15:55.329 --> 15:58.414
You can't kill me, man.
It's not part of the deal.

15:58.624 --> 15:59.749
Silence.

16:01.377 --> 16:02.961
[SHOUTS]

16:08.676 --> 16:12.345
I'm an Original. Show a little respect.

16:18.435 --> 16:21.396
The moment you cease to be
of use to me, you're dead...

16:21.855 --> 16:25.400
...so you should do what I say.

16:25.859 --> 16:27.735
Keep Elena safe.

16:39.581 --> 16:41.416
My dad did all the cooking too.

16:41.583 --> 16:43.084
- And your mom?
- She sat right here...

16:43.252 --> 16:45.253
...and watched.
- Heh.

16:45.421 --> 16:46.838
She couldn't cook either.

16:50.884 --> 16:52.343
Fire's dying.

16:52.511 --> 16:54.178
Oh, yeah. I will get more wood.

16:54.346 --> 16:56.097
- I got it.
- No, no. It's cold outside.

16:56.265 --> 16:58.057
Hey.

16:58.225 --> 17:01.019
So I'll get a jacket.

17:20.289 --> 17:21.372
My mom's perfume.

17:26.878 --> 17:29.797
Jenna was supposed
to pack all this up...

17:30.591 --> 17:32.091
...but she kept putting it off.

17:35.262 --> 17:37.138
I don't blame her.

17:39.767 --> 17:41.392
Here.

17:42.561 --> 17:44.145
Bundle up.

17:44.563 --> 17:45.938
It was my great-granddad's.

17:47.316 --> 17:49.067
And you look very hot in it.

17:50.235 --> 17:54.989
I look hot in your dead
great-granddad's jacket?

17:55.157 --> 17:57.075
Beyond hot, heh.

18:01.330 --> 18:03.998
Stefan. It's my parents' bedroom.

18:04.166 --> 18:06.584
STEFAN: Mm.
- Heh.

18:11.340 --> 18:12.965
Heh, what?

18:15.511 --> 18:16.677
- Huh?
- What?

18:16.845 --> 18:19.472
This is hollow inside.

18:35.531 --> 18:36.614
What is it?

18:39.785 --> 18:42.120
A really good hiding place.

19:00.889 --> 19:02.890
Oh, my God.

19:03.058 --> 19:05.810
We only have an hour or two
before my mom gets home...

19:05.978 --> 19:07.645
...and these are all I could find.

19:07.813 --> 19:09.522
Place these evenly around the room.

19:09.857 --> 19:11.149
How does this work?

19:11.400 --> 19:15.486
Um, I'll put him in a trance
and ask him questions. It's...

19:15.654 --> 19:16.737
It's like hypnosis.

19:16.905 --> 19:21.325
- You sure you're strong enough for this?
- That's what the candles are for.

19:21.493 --> 19:24.203
- I'll draw power from the flames.
- I'll get the matches.

19:24.371 --> 19:25.913
I got it.

19:28.375 --> 19:29.750
Never gonna get used to that.

19:29.918 --> 19:32.003
Oh, come on.
That's pretty hot and you know it.

19:32.171 --> 19:35.506
- I need a bowl of water.
- Yeah, yeah. I'll, uh, go get it.

19:39.052 --> 19:41.762
Okay, what was that? It's hot?

19:41.930 --> 19:44.515
He is so crushing on you.

19:44.683 --> 19:46.350
- So?
- So?

19:46.518 --> 19:50.021
What, you'd rather be
with traitor warlock over here?

19:50.189 --> 19:52.607
I'm not into Luka. It's just...

19:52.774 --> 19:58.529
...you know, he understood me
and he was new and different.

19:58.697 --> 20:01.699
And you've known Jeremy
since forever...

20:01.867 --> 20:04.368
...and you only see him one way,
as Elena's brother.

20:05.078 --> 20:07.747
But you're a witch and I'm a vampire.

20:07.915 --> 20:10.291
You know, it's not like
we're in any position to...

20:10.459 --> 20:12.251
- To be picky.
- No.

20:12.419 --> 20:13.461
[BOTH LAUGH]

20:13.629 --> 20:15.755
To judge.

20:26.975 --> 20:28.601
Looks like he's waking up.

20:40.489 --> 20:42.448
- Today was a bust.
- Yeah.

20:42.616 --> 20:44.450
- How's the throat?
- Sore.

20:44.618 --> 20:46.452
Yeah, that Elijah's one scary dude.

20:47.412 --> 20:48.996
But with nice hair.

20:49.206 --> 20:51.666
Hey, you want another one?

20:53.085 --> 20:55.836
Ugh, he's gonna be hard to kill.

20:56.004 --> 20:58.798
Yeah. I'd think twice
before I'd trust that dagger...

20:58.966 --> 21:01.509
...and some ashes to do the job.

21:01.718 --> 21:04.929
- You're gonna need more info.
- I'm out of sources.

21:05.931 --> 21:07.682
What's up with you
and this news chick?

21:07.849 --> 21:09.058
Ooh.

21:10.269 --> 21:11.686
She's got spunk, huh?

21:13.438 --> 21:16.941
- Just don't kill her, please.
- If I did, who would report her death?

21:17.109 --> 21:20.695
Just don't do it, all right?
She's friends with Jenna...

21:20.862 --> 21:23.364
...and it's bad enough
I'm lying about everything.

21:23.532 --> 21:25.700
I hate the lies.

21:26.201 --> 21:29.328
Oh, God. I gotta go.
I gotta pick Jenna up.

21:29.663 --> 21:31.539
Don't worry. I'll, uh, show myself out.

21:32.040 --> 21:33.791
Good luck.

21:40.549 --> 21:42.008
[CRASH]

21:44.219 --> 21:45.720
[ALARIC GRUNTING]

21:54.896 --> 21:56.856
[GRUNTING AND SHOUTING]

22:14.041 --> 22:15.916
Whew. Damn, you're strong.

22:16.835 --> 22:18.544
It took the whole syringe.

22:22.674 --> 22:24.925
Grab that one. He's dead.

22:26.845 --> 22:28.846
Hi, Damon.

22:30.182 --> 22:31.849
Nice to see you again.

22:36.980 --> 22:39.940
These must be
the other Johnathan Gilbert journals.

22:40.108 --> 22:44.570
Jeremy had the one
but John said that there were others.

22:44.988 --> 22:47.239
His whole life's in here.

22:50.243 --> 22:54.830
I'll go get the firewood.
Let you have a moment.

23:06.301 --> 23:07.635
[CELL PHONE CHIMES]

23:07.803 --> 23:09.637
We're good to go.

23:15.811 --> 23:16.936
You up for this?

23:23.693 --> 23:24.735
[BRADY SIGHS]

23:25.612 --> 23:29.490
These people have done nothing
but lie to you.

23:30.158 --> 23:34.328
This girl that you've known since birth,
she's with the vampires now...

23:34.496 --> 23:36.163
...the ones who killed Mason.

23:37.833 --> 23:39.125
They're the enemy...

23:39.751 --> 23:42.503
...and if they break that curse...

23:44.297 --> 23:46.841
...well, all of us are as good as dead.

23:51.847 --> 23:53.848
Are you up for this?

23:56.643 --> 23:59.520
- Yes.
- Good.

24:00.355 --> 24:04.316
Because if you wuss out, you're gonna
have me to deal with, you got it?

24:17.414 --> 24:20.207
- Where's Elena?
- At the lake house for the weekend.

24:20.375 --> 24:22.877
- With Stefan.
- Yes, with Stefan.

24:23.044 --> 24:26.380
- Who gave her permission for that?
- I did. Until you get a lawyer...

24:26.548 --> 24:29.758
...file for guardianship, it's my call,
there's nothing you can do.

24:29.926 --> 24:33.929
I always knew you were lax with them
but I didn't think you were negligent.

24:34.097 --> 24:38.058
She wanted to get away from you, okay?
And so do I, so I'll be staying with Ric.

24:38.226 --> 24:40.895
Because he's such a great guy, right?

24:41.062 --> 24:42.605
You are on dangerous ground.

24:43.023 --> 24:44.899
- He's a liar, Jenna.
- What?

24:45.066 --> 24:47.234
Did he tell you
what happened to his wife?

24:47.736 --> 24:49.737
- She died.
- Really?

24:50.113 --> 24:52.281
So they found her body?

24:52.449 --> 24:53.741
What are you saying?

24:54.201 --> 24:58.621
Why don't you ask Ric?
I'd love to hear his answer.

24:59.122 --> 25:00.748
Have a great night.

25:13.720 --> 25:14.970
[GRUNTS]

25:29.277 --> 25:31.278
- Morning, sunshine.
- Oh.

25:31.988 --> 25:35.658
I saw this movie once,
some torture-porn flick.

25:35.867 --> 25:39.495
Anyway, they had this collar device
that was, heh, really cool...

25:39.663 --> 25:44.458
...so I just modified it some with some
wooden nails, and when I pull...

25:44.834 --> 25:46.502
[GROANING]

25:48.296 --> 25:51.465
So I hear you have the moonstone.

25:55.762 --> 25:57.388
[CHUCKLES]

25:59.140 --> 26:02.643
Oh, if you only knew the irony
of this moment right now.

26:05.522 --> 26:08.315
Let me tell you how this is gonna go.

26:08.525 --> 26:12.820
You're gonna torture me, I don't talk,
someone loses a heart.

26:12.988 --> 26:15.322
Last time, it was your boy Mason.

26:17.158 --> 26:20.661
This time, it'll be you.

26:22.247 --> 26:24.290
[GROANING]

26:25.792 --> 26:29.336
- How long is this gonna take?
- I don't know. He's fighting me.

26:29.504 --> 26:30.796
Please stop.

26:31.506 --> 26:33.340
Please.

26:39.347 --> 26:41.515
Yeah. All right.

26:43.310 --> 26:45.227
Why are you working with Elijah?

26:45.437 --> 26:47.563
Klaus.

26:48.523 --> 26:50.691
We both want him dead.

26:54.571 --> 26:58.157
You wanna kill Klaus too. Why?

26:58.325 --> 27:02.703
Because he has her
and we have to get her away from him.

27:02.871 --> 27:05.664
- Who are you talking about?
- My sister.

27:06.541 --> 27:07.958
His sister?

27:08.710 --> 27:10.336
Why does he have her?

27:10.503 --> 27:15.382
He's searching for a way to undo
the curse without the doppelgänger.

27:16.217 --> 27:21.847
He's forced generations of witches
to help him for centuries.

27:22.015 --> 27:24.058
What has Elijah promised you?

27:24.225 --> 27:30.064
If we help Elijah kill Klaus,
he's promised to return her to us.

27:30.231 --> 27:32.232
BONNIE:
And how do you kill Klaus?

27:32.400 --> 27:35.903
How do you kill an Original vampire?

27:37.572 --> 27:41.075
He'll kill me if I tell you.
Don't make me.

27:41.242 --> 27:43.786
It's okay, Bonnie,
we can find another way.

27:43.995 --> 27:45.412
No.

27:50.001 --> 27:51.919
How will you kill Klaus?

27:52.087 --> 27:55.589
After the sacrifice,
Klaus will be vulnerable, weak.

27:55.757 --> 27:56.924
It's our only chance.

27:57.092 --> 27:59.510
After the sacrifice?

28:00.261 --> 28:03.138
What do you mean "after"?

28:03.640 --> 28:05.432
Klaus will be vulnerable.

28:07.560 --> 28:09.603
But Elena will be dead.

28:09.771 --> 28:11.438
LUKA:
Yes.

28:12.399 --> 28:14.108
Elena has to die.

28:18.905 --> 28:20.030
No.

28:24.160 --> 28:25.619
[PANTS]

28:38.842 --> 28:40.384
[GRUNTING]

28:46.474 --> 28:48.475
BRADY:
Keep him down.

28:50.103 --> 28:52.146
If he moves...

28:52.981 --> 28:54.148
...kill him.

29:05.952 --> 29:07.578
Don't move.

29:07.746 --> 29:10.873
Help me get the bullet out.
It punctured my heart.

29:11.040 --> 29:13.625
I need to get it out.
I'm not gonna fight you.

29:13.835 --> 29:15.043
I don't think so.

29:15.211 --> 29:17.588
Tyler, why are you doing this?

29:17.756 --> 29:20.048
I can't let you break the curse.

29:22.093 --> 29:25.137
- You know about the curse?
- You're liars, all of you.

29:25.346 --> 29:26.722
No, I swear to you.

29:26.890 --> 29:29.516
We don't wanna break the curse.
We don't wanna do that.

29:29.684 --> 29:31.185
Oh, yeah?

29:33.021 --> 29:34.104
But I do.

29:34.522 --> 29:36.982
[GROANING]

29:37.150 --> 29:38.859
I can't be like this forever.

29:39.903 --> 29:42.446
Tyler, I'm just trying to save Elena.

29:42.614 --> 29:44.239
Elena will be fine.

29:45.950 --> 29:48.410
They didn't tell you that part,
did they?

29:48.578 --> 29:51.288
- Who are the liars now?
- Tell me what?

29:51.623 --> 29:55.876
In order to break the curse,
Elena has to die.

30:03.802 --> 30:05.969
Are you growing the trees out there?

30:21.236 --> 30:23.070
Stefan?

30:37.919 --> 30:40.921
Stefan, what are you doing out there?

30:41.089 --> 30:42.172
[GASPS]

30:42.340 --> 30:43.632
[BRADY GROANING]

31:05.738 --> 31:08.073
I can smell you.

31:29.137 --> 31:30.971
[SNIFFS]

32:12.847 --> 32:14.973
[ELENA YELLS AND BRADY GRUNTS]

32:24.025 --> 32:25.776
[ELENA PANTING]

32:25.944 --> 32:27.277
[BRADY GRUNTS]

32:32.784 --> 32:36.453
It's okay. It's okay.
You're okay. You're okay.

32:36.621 --> 32:39.706
You're okay. It's okay.

32:44.045 --> 32:45.796
Tyler?

32:47.548 --> 32:51.426
I didn't know what
they were gonna do to you. I didn't.

32:51.636 --> 32:53.303
I just...

32:54.263 --> 32:57.057
I don't wanna be like this anymore.

33:05.316 --> 33:06.900
I'm sorry, Elena.

33:07.068 --> 33:08.860
ELENA:
It's okay.

33:11.739 --> 33:14.950
[SIGHS]

33:16.661 --> 33:19.371
You know what the great thing
about buckshot is?

33:19.580 --> 33:23.834
It scatters through the body.
Maximum damage.

33:26.379 --> 33:28.630
- Where's the moonstone?
- Get over it, honey.

33:28.798 --> 33:30.424
You're never gonna get it.

33:30.591 --> 33:32.384
ELIJAH:
You looking for this?

33:48.693 --> 33:50.694
Go ahead. Take it.

33:50.862 --> 33:51.903
[ROARS]

33:52.071 --> 33:53.530
[GRUNTS]

33:56.451 --> 33:57.909
[GRUNTING]

34:03.875 --> 34:06.668
What about you, sweetheart, huh?

34:07.712 --> 34:09.545
Wanna take a shot?

34:09.714 --> 34:11.422
No? Yes? No?

34:11.632 --> 34:12.716
Where's the girl?

34:13.467 --> 34:15.135
I don't know.

34:16.012 --> 34:17.846
It doesn't really matter.

34:20.266 --> 34:21.641
[STEVIE GRUNTS]

34:31.152 --> 34:35.155
So you realize this is the third time
I've saved your life now?

34:49.712 --> 34:52.172
So he planned to kill her all along.

34:52.340 --> 34:55.217
Yeah, the sacrifice
is part of Elijah's plan.

34:55.384 --> 34:58.011
Got it. Loud and clear.

34:59.055 --> 35:00.764
- Finally.
- Unh.

35:00.973 --> 35:03.475
You missed all the fun.

35:08.356 --> 35:10.065
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

35:15.488 --> 35:17.572
There you are. Are you okay?

35:17.740 --> 35:18.865
ALARIC [OVER PHONE]:
Yeah, sorry.

35:19.033 --> 35:21.868
Er, I've just been grading papers.

35:22.036 --> 35:23.328
[GRUNTS]

35:23.496 --> 35:24.913
Honestly...

35:25.206 --> 35:26.206
Uh...

35:28.084 --> 35:29.793
I fell asleep. I'm sorry.

35:30.002 --> 35:31.586
Jenna, I'm a jerk.

35:31.754 --> 35:34.548
No, it's fine.
I'm just glad you're okay.

35:34.715 --> 35:37.884
So, uh, tomorrow, I'm all yours, okay?

35:38.052 --> 35:40.637
Sure. Sounds great.

35:40.805 --> 35:44.391
- All right. Good night, Jenna.
- Good night.

35:50.231 --> 35:52.065
DAMON: It was straight
from the witch's mouth.

35:52.400 --> 35:54.734
He was gonna go through
with the whole sacrifice.

35:54.902 --> 35:56.903
You should keep her away
a little longer.

35:57.071 --> 36:01.283
- Be careful, try not to get yourself killed.
DAMON: Yeah, it's been a day for that.

36:07.456 --> 36:09.249
It was, um... That was Damon.

36:09.417 --> 36:11.334
- We need to talk.
- What is it?

36:11.544 --> 36:15.922
He learned that Elijah's planning
for you to die in the sacrifice ritual.

36:16.549 --> 36:18.091
[SIGHS]

36:19.260 --> 36:21.595
I know the deal I made, Stefan.

36:21.762 --> 36:24.806
Elijah's very careful with his words.

36:25.099 --> 36:29.853
He promised to protect my friends.
He never said a word about me.

36:30.062 --> 36:31.688
You mean...

36:32.815 --> 36:35.650
...that you knew
that you weren't gonna survive this?

36:35.818 --> 36:39.654
If it comes down to the people
that I love getting killed or me...

36:40.281 --> 36:42.616
...I know what my choice is gonna be.

36:42.783 --> 36:44.534
Elena, how...?

36:44.702 --> 36:47.787
How could you stand out there
earlier with me...

36:47.955 --> 36:51.499
...talking about our future when you
don't even expect to have one.

36:51.667 --> 36:55.670
I'm sorry, Stefan. I'm just trying to keep
the people that I love safe.

36:55.838 --> 36:57.339
I'm trying to keep you safe.

36:57.506 --> 36:59.966
No, what you're doing
is you're being a martyr.

37:00.134 --> 37:04.012
How is that any different from when you
say that you would die to keep me safe?

37:04.180 --> 37:05.722
Because I've already lived.

37:05.890 --> 37:09.142
A hundred and sixty-two years
I have lived and you've barely begun.

37:09.310 --> 37:11.853
And now you wanna let yourself
get killed?

37:13.481 --> 37:15.649
That's not heroic.

37:16.234 --> 37:18.318
It's tragic.

37:23.491 --> 37:25.033
So will Luka remember anything?

37:25.201 --> 37:28.245
No. He'll know he lost consciousness,
that's all.

37:28.412 --> 37:30.080
Well, should we wait for Caroline?

37:30.248 --> 37:33.250
She was just gonna drop Luka back
at the Grill.

37:33.417 --> 37:35.210
Said to lock the door on our way out.

37:35.378 --> 37:38.672
Yeah, well, I hope she drops him hard.

37:39.257 --> 37:40.757
Wait.

37:44.220 --> 37:47.430
You're Elena's little brother,
I've known you forever.

37:48.140 --> 37:49.599
You're that punk kid.

37:49.767 --> 37:53.853
I remember your awkward, heh, phase
and then your emo phase...

37:54.021 --> 37:56.731
...your druggie phase and...
- Heh.

37:56.899 --> 38:00.777
...overnight, you turned into this hot guy
who's really sweet and...

38:00.945 --> 38:02.153
You think I'm hot?

38:04.699 --> 38:09.953
With everything that's going on,
you know, the curses and sacrifice...

38:10.162 --> 38:11.579
Enough already.

38:23.467 --> 38:24.634
Wow.

38:24.802 --> 38:26.219
[CHUCKLES]

38:32.018 --> 38:33.643
[CREAKING NEARBY]

38:34.770 --> 38:41.943
Hello?

38:58.502 --> 39:00.086
Matt.

39:01.714 --> 39:04.215
- I'm not in the mood, man.
- I need to say something.

39:04.592 --> 39:06.259
All right. Say it.

39:06.427 --> 39:10.430
I've been going through a rough time,
something I can't really talk about...

39:10.765 --> 39:12.932
...and Caroline's been helping me
through it.

39:13.100 --> 39:17.771
She's been there for me more than
anyone's ever been there my entire life...

39:18.939 --> 39:20.440
...and I kind of fell for her.

39:21.609 --> 39:25.445
I don't know how anyone wouldn't
because she's pretty incredible.

39:28.616 --> 39:30.617
But she loves you...

39:31.494 --> 39:33.161
...and she needs you...

39:34.288 --> 39:36.289
...and to be honest...

39:36.624 --> 39:39.042
...she deserves someone like you.

39:41.295 --> 39:43.463
So you be good to her...

39:43.798 --> 39:45.340
...okay?

39:45.800 --> 39:48.301
Yeah, man. Of course.

39:50.805 --> 39:52.680
See you around, Matt.

39:53.182 --> 39:54.808
Yeah.

40:06.570 --> 40:08.279
Mom?

40:46.610 --> 40:48.319
[SIGHS]

40:50.197 --> 40:52.365
I'm sorry about Brady
and your friends...

40:53.200 --> 40:54.868
...but if I'm gonna go with you...

40:55.536 --> 40:57.537
...no more lies.

40:59.123 --> 41:01.249
No more lies.

41:04.086 --> 41:05.962
You're doing the right thing.

41:07.381 --> 41:09.549
I can't stay here...

41:10.926 --> 41:12.719
...not like this.

41:52.343 --> 41:54.344
[English - US - SDH]
